HSBC Global Asset Management (Hong Kong) Ltd

- Hong Kong
				
				






























									
																			
						HSBC Global Asset Management is the asset management business of the HSBC Group, specializing in working with clients or their advisors to design and deliver despoke investment solutions. Through its network of offices in over 30 countries and territories around the world, HSBC Global Asset Management has a worldwide client base of private clients, intermediaries, corporates and institutions invested in both segregated accounts and pooled funds.HSBC Global Asset Management manages assets totalling US$453 billion, and is a leader in emerging markets, with US$139 billion invested in this asset class. In Hong Kong, HSBC Global Asset Mabagement is the largest Mandatory Provident Fund asset manager (All data as at 30 June 2011).
					
				





Company Profile












Number of Staff (HK):
101-200








Year of Establishment:

1973







Nature of Business:

																		
																					
											Service Company
																			
									







Major Market(s):


										
											Central & South America, 
										
